4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT SUPPORTING THE PREVENTION OF CARDIAC ARREST IN
5 YOUTH ATHLETES; REQUIRING THE SUPERINTENDENT OF PUBLIC INSTRUCTION TO DEVELOP
6 RESOURCES; REQUIRING COACHES TO UNDERGO TRAINING ON CARDIAC ARREST; REQUIRING
7 COACHES TO HOLD INFORMATIONAL MEETINGS ON CARDIAC ARREST; ALLOWING COACHES,
8 TRAINERS, AND OFFICIALS TO REMOVE A YOUTH ATHLETE FROM PARTICIPATION IF THE YOUTH
9 ATHLETE EXHIBITS WARNING SIGNS OF CARDIAC ARREST; REQUIRING A YOUTH ATHLETE
10 REMOVED FROM PARTICIPATION TO BE CLEARED BY A MEDICAL PROFESSIONAL PRIOR TO
11 RETURNING TO PLAY; CLARIFYING THAT THE PURCHASE OF AUTOMATIC EXTERNAL
12 DEFIBRILLATORS IS ALLOWED AS AN ENHANCEMENT TO SCHOOL AND STUDENT SAFETY AND
13 SECURITY AND IS THEREFORE AN ALLOWABLE EXPENDITURE FOR SCHOOL MAJOR MAINTENANCE
14 AID; PROVIDING A DEFINITION; PROVIDING AN APPROPRIATION; AMENDING SECTIONS 20-9-236 AND
15 20-9-502, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.”
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
18
19 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Cardiac arrest response for youth athletes -- purpose --
20 requirements of schools and superintendent of public instruction. (1) The purposes of this section are to:
21 (a) support, adopt, and implement a cardiac emergency response plan in schools that integrates
22 evidence-based core elements in accordance with the American heart association guidelines or other nationally
23 recognized, evidence-based standards;
24 (b) raise awareness among parents of youth athletes about the risks related to cardiac arrest; and
25 (c) ensure that coaches, athletic trainers, and athletic officials understand the risks of cardiac
26 arrest in youth athletes and that they are trained in cardiopulmonary resuscitation, first aid, and the use of an
27 automatic external defibrillator.
28 (2) The superintendent of public instruction, after consultation with experts in cardiac arrest
