1 (viii) reviewing and evaluating the plan regularly and annually.
2 (4) Each school year, before a youth athletic activity season begins:
3 (a) a school district or nonpublic school shall inform each coach of the coach's duties under this
4 section; and
5 (b) the coach of a youth athletic activity shall:
6 (i) obtain and maintain certification in cardiopulmonary resuscitation, first aid, and the use of an
7 automatic external defibrillator. Certification in cardiopulmonary resuscitation and the use of an automatic
8 external defibrillator must be consistent with nationally recognized, evidence-based emergency cardiovascular
9 care guidelines.
10 (ii) hold an informational meeting for students, parents, and assistant coaches before each athletic
11 season regarding the symptoms and warning signs of sudden cardiac arrest, which may include presentations
12 from physicians, pediatric cardiologists, and athletic trainers as well as the information sheet provided under
13 subsection (2).
14 (5) (a) If an athletic trainer, official, or coach reasonably believes a student is exhibiting symptoms
15 or warning signs of sudden cardiac arrest, the coach may remove the student from participation in a youth
16 athletic activity.
17 (b) If the student is removed from participation in the youth athletic activity, the coach shall attempt
18 to notify the student's parent or legal guardian.
19 (6) A student who is removed from participation in a youth athletic activity under subsection (5)
20 may not participate in a youth athletic activity until the student has been evaluated by and received written
21 clearance from a licensed physician, physician assistant, or nurse practitioner.
22 (7) The sponsor of a recreational youth athletic activity may follow the guidelines provided under
23 this section.
24 (8) As used in this section, "youth athletic activity" means:
25 (a) interscholastic athletics;
26 (b) an athletic contest or competition, other than interscholastic athletics, that is sponsored by or
27 associated with a school district or a nonpublic school, including competitive and noncompetitive cheerleading;
28 (c) any sports activity sponsored by a school-affiliated club; or
